    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death). Testing conducted at ambient laboratory temperature (20–23 °C), atmospheric pressure (101.3 kPa ± 2%), quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min), and dry cortical-bone-surrogate block material (UHMWPE, density 0.94 g/cm³). All experimental runs performed within these parameter bounds, providing a de facto operational window for the validation dataset.",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium"
  },
