    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for a Medium model risk, Class II device. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because all three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) and the single-condition protocol is consistent with ASTM F1717 standard practice. Overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission.",
